# Paper Hub AI Rules

## Frontend / CSS Guidelines

### Prefer predefined CSS classes over inline styles
- Do NOT use inline `style={{ ... }}` in JSX/TSX unless unavoidable.
- Rely on Bootstrap 5.3 utility classes and custom CSS from `app.css`.
- Add new reusable CSS classes to `frontend/src/styles/app.css` as needed.

### Dark mode compatibility
- The app uses Bootstrap 5.3's native `data-bs-theme` for light/dark mode.
- Use CSS variables (`var(--bs-body-bg)`, `var(--bs-body-color)`, etc.) for colors, backgrounds, borders.
- Never hardcode color values like `white`, `#ccc`, `#eee`, `#f5f5f5` — they break in dark mode.
- Use CSS `:hover` instead of inline `onMouseEnter`/`onMouseLeave` for hover effects.

### Styling hierarchy (preference order)
1. Bootstrap utility class
2. Custom CSS class in `app.css`
3. Inline style (last resort)
